        <name>16.3.1.3 binomial coefficients</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a real number \(x\) approaches zero we note hiigher powers of&amp;nbsp; \(x\) become even closer to zero and may even fall within a margin of error we can tolerate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assume, for this exercise, that \(x^3\) and higher powers may be ignored in comparison to lower order terms. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Find a quadratic polynomial approximating \( (1&#8722;x)^{{@pp@}} \). Hint:&amp;nbsp;First expand \( (1+x)^{{@pp@}} \) using the binomial series with \(p=\displaystyle{@pp@} \)and with \( x \) replaced by \( (&#8722;x) \):&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\( (1-x)^{@pp@} \approx \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;"&gt;The binomial series gives \[ (x-1)^{@pp@} \approx {@ta@}.\]&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;"&gt;What we have done in this exercise is to approximate the function \((1-x)^{{@pp@}}\) by the simpler (polynomial) function \(\displaystyle {@ta@}\) which is reasonable provided \(x\) is very small.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;In the case of \((1-x)^{\frac{1}{2}}\)this approximation is well illustrated geometrically by drawing the curves \(y=(1-x)^{\frac{1}{2}}\) and \(y=1-\dfrac{1}{2}x-\dfrac{1}{8}x^2\). The two curves coincide when \(x\) is &#8216;small&#8217;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/quadratic%20polynomial%20graph.svg" alt="plot of x minus 1 over 8 x squared with dotted line 1 minus x all to the power of a half" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom" width="457" height="195"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
